00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:44,669
{\an8}<i>Viktor Valtrovi and family.</i>

2
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:47,630
{\an8}<i>This is really who everyone</i>
<i>has been waiting for.</i>

3
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:51,384
{\an8}<i>Their only daughter.</i>

4
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:55,138
{\an8}<i>The biggest secret of the Czech Republic</i>

5
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:56,723
{\an8}<i>is about to be revealed!</i>

6
00:00:56,806 --> 00:00:58,767
{\an8}<i>Chiara Valtrovi!</i>

7
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:08,234
{\an8}Chiara!

8
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:10,904
{\an8}Chiara!

9
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:46,898
{\an8}Mikoy!

10
00:01:51,444 --> 00:01:53,363
Bring them there!

11
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:57,659
{\an8}What happened?

12
00:01:57,742 --> 00:01:59,160
{\an8}Something exploded loudly!

13
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:01,037
{\an8}There are people with guns.

14
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:03,248
{\an8}- How many are there?
- A lot!

15
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:05,416
{\an8}Wait. Hide! Hide!

16
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,960
{\an8}What exploded?

17
00:02:07,043 --> 00:02:08,503
{\an8}Let’s go back inside.

18
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:10,547
{\an8}- Why?
- Go inside.

19
00:02:27,355 --> 00:02:28,273
{\an8}No! Viktor!

20
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,694
{\an8}Viktor!

21
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:38,825
{\an8}- Who are all of you?
- Gotcha!

22
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:42,495
{\an8}Viktor!

23
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,583
{\an8}We have been here for a while.

24
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:48,293
{\an8}Maybe we can go out now.

25
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:50,378
{\an8}- Tess, please keep quiet.
- Maybe it’s okay now.

26
00:02:50,461 --> 00:02:52,005
{\an8}Wait, it’s not safe outside yet.

27
00:02:52,088 --> 00:02:53,840
{\an8}Mario, our kids… What about Mikoy?

28
00:02:53,923 --> 00:02:56,009
{\an8}- Yes, wait… I’m thinking.
- Your son is alone there.

29
00:02:57,719 --> 00:03:00,763
- Viktor!
- All good.

30
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,056
Let me go!

31
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,141
Viktor!

32
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:05,101
Hey! Let go!

33
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:06,853
- That’s enough!
- Come on!

34
00:03:06,936 --> 00:03:08,521
I don’t want to!

35
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:10,481
Viktor!

36
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:12,358
- Get inside!
- Fine!

37
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:16,195
- Are you leaving me here?
- Tess, just a moment.

38
00:03:16,279 --> 00:03:17,488
- Ma’am, sir, please go inside!
- I'll go with you.

39
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:20,033
Don’t go outside! It’s too dangerous.

40
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:21,117
- Our children are out there.
- All right…

41
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,702
- They’re out there!
- We’ll handle it.

42
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:24,495
- All right.
- Please go inside, sir.

43
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:25,914
Come on!

44
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:33,212
Is this the right place we came to?

45
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:35,256
Is this really the party venue?

46
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:38,468
But this doesn’t look like a party.

47
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,178
Looks like a disaster.

48
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:42,305
- It's coming!
- Hurry!

49
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:51,314
What about Mom and Dad? And my brother?

50
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:52,649
Oh my God, they’re inside!

51
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:55,193
- Come on. Let’s help them!
- Angelito.

52
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:56,736
Listen carefully.

53
00:03:56,819 --> 00:03:59,280
I understand that you’re worried.

54
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:02,742
But right now,
the best way to help your family

55
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:04,661
is for us to find a safe place.

56
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:09,123
If there really is a bomb,

57
00:04:09,207 --> 00:04:12,543
it’s just a delay tactic
to cause panic among everyone.

58
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:13,962
You mean,

59
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:17,882
those explosions were just the intro?

60
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:18,925
The chaos isn’t over yet?

61
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:24,097
We’re not sure.

62
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:26,266
Not until the mission is accomplished.

63
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:28,601
Mission? What mission?

64
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:36,985
Whether the target
is meant to be dead or alive.

65
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:43,074
They kidnapped Donabel,
but I put a tracker on her.

66
00:04:43,157 --> 00:04:44,325
Okay, go after them.

67
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:46,244
- Okay.
- Go, go, go.

68
00:04:57,130 --> 00:05:00,800
My son! Take care of him… Mikoy!

69
00:05:00,883 --> 00:05:02,176
- Mikoy!
- What happened?

70
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:03,761
Mikoy!

71
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,851
Mikoy! You'll get through it!

72
00:05:09,934 --> 00:05:11,436
My child!

73
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:13,438
He will make it. He will make it.

74
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:16,357
Mikoy, wait-- Doc!

75
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:17,608
Doc, please help my son.

76
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:20,403
Yes, just wait. We understand.
Yes. We will do our best.

77
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:22,113
We’ll keep you updated, but we’re sorry,

78
00:05:22,196 --> 00:05:23,656
you can’t stay here.

79
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:27,076
Tess.

80
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,078
Whatever happens to Mikoy,

81
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:30,913
he can handle it.

82
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:33,291
He’ll get through this.

83
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:39,338
My child.

84
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,719
‪I can't take this…

85
00:05:46,971 --> 00:05:49,098
- Take him inside.
- Doc.

86
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:57,815
{\an8}I need any information
that we can gather from our lawyer.

87
00:05:57,899 --> 00:05:59,484
Anything. I need to gather them.

88
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,528
So… Okay, please.

89
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:04,822
- Yes. Please wait for the nurse.
- Chiara?

90
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:07,200
Help us pray, my child.

91
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:09,327
Let’s pray for Mikoy, my child.

92
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:38,189
…to get information about everything…

93
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:45,613
Do you think I care who you are?

94
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:24,193
Please treat Mr. Valtrovi. He’s injured.

95
00:07:27,655 --> 00:07:28,656
Who are you?

96
00:07:28,739 --> 00:07:30,491
Who are you? What do you want from me?

97
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:32,869
Why are you doing this to me?

98
00:07:34,328 --> 00:07:36,456
What do you want?

99
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,499
Money? You want money?

100
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:42,587
Just one call to my husband… Come on.

101
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:48,926
He's easy to talk to, you know.

102
00:07:56,517 --> 00:07:58,644
You know the saying,

103
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:02,648
"You reap what you sow."

104
00:08:03,941 --> 00:08:07,612
And now we’re here to make you pay

105
00:08:07,695 --> 00:08:09,864
for all the suffering your husband caused.

106
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,246
Once there’s an update,

107
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,582
inform me right away.

108
00:08:29,383 --> 00:08:30,218
What did they say?

109
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:31,594
Angelito.

110
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:34,180
Listen to me carefully.

111
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:37,308
Prepare yourself. Okay?

112
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:41,187
Your brother Mikoy is at the hospital.

113
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:44,190
He was shot.

114
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,615
Where’s my brother Mikoy?

115
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,409
He’s in the operating room.

116
00:08:55,493 --> 00:08:57,203
We’re still waiting for an update.

117
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:01,165
Mom, Dad.

118
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,960
What happened?

119
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:09,340
What matters is we’re all here for Mikoy.

120
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,467
That's what matters.

121
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:14,762
My child.

122
00:09:14,845 --> 00:09:18,391
Let’s offer more prayers for your brother.

123
00:09:18,474 --> 00:09:19,559
Yes.

124
00:09:22,853 --> 00:09:23,980
Dad!

125
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,902
I’m okay, child. I’m okay.

126
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:33,364
Where is he?

127
00:09:38,035 --> 00:09:41,914
I was praying so hard it wasn’t one of us.

128
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:44,542
Mikoy is still in the OR.

129
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:03,978
They took your mother.

130
00:10:13,904 --> 00:10:15,531
Just one call to my husband…

131
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:20,202
I’ll call him.

132
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,206
he’ll find a way
to handle whatever this is.

133
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:33,674
Do you even know us, Donabel?

134
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:35,968
Do you know what we need?

135
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:38,804
Whatever it is that you need,

136
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:39,847
I’m easy to deal with.

137
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:46,646
that what we need
is to see your husband dead?

138
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:58,783
I’m so sorry.

139
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,951
You got dragged into this mess.

140
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:03,996
We’re the same.

141
00:11:04,747 --> 00:11:06,457
We’re all victims here.

142
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:11,045
The truth is,

143
00:11:11,962 --> 00:11:15,508
I’m just as confused as you are.

144
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:18,844
They took your mom,

145
00:11:19,553 --> 00:11:21,430
and the police aren’t doing anything.

146
00:11:23,599 --> 00:11:24,975
You know, Viktor,

147
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:30,106
if you haven’t received
any ransom note or ransom demand,

148
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:33,025
chances are Donabel is still alive.

149
00:11:39,073 --> 00:11:39,907
Your mother

150
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:43,369
means everything to me.

151
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,037
I don’t know…

152
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:48,249
I don’t know what I’ll do…

153
00:11:50,584 --> 00:11:51,585
without her.

154
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:57,007
Let’s talk this out calmly.

155
00:11:57,091 --> 00:11:58,467
So everyone can be happy!

156
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:08,727
It must be your sense of humor

157
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:11,480
that attracted someone like Viktor to you.

158
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:15,484
Do you think it’s funny
what your husband did to us?

159
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:26,996
<i>He built the Moraviano</i>
<i>without notice or permission.</i>

160
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:29,165
You are no longer allowed
to pass through this route!

161
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:34,253
No notice at all,

162
00:12:34,962 --> 00:12:38,382
and no regard or respect.

163
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:41,010
Kneel!

164
00:12:41,093 --> 00:12:42,428
Kneel, I said!

165
00:12:42,511 --> 00:12:45,139
<i>You and your husband destroyed everything.</i>

166
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:48,058
<i>Not just property, but countless families.</i>

167
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:49,435
<i>For what?</i>

168
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:51,520
<i>To act like kings.</i>

169
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:55,608
<i>To control every territory.</i>

170
00:12:55,691 --> 00:12:59,987
And worst of all, a Filipino like you,

171
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:03,908
his accomplice, crushing our dignity,

172
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:07,620
stealing everything we worked for.

173
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:10,789
Why are you smiling?

174
00:13:11,707 --> 00:13:13,792
Do you think this is funny,

175
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:15,878
what your husband did?

176
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:17,171
No.

177
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:19,089
It's just weird.

178
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:20,633
You act all righteous,

179
00:13:20,716 --> 00:13:22,927
but you’re just a criminal.

180
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:24,261
You got outplayed

181
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:26,805
by a better criminal than you.

182
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:27,932
My husband.

183
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:41,904
How is my child, Doc?

184
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,697
He sustained a gunshot wound.

185
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:44,782
We operated immediately

186
00:13:44,865 --> 00:13:47,618
to remove the bullet
and repair the damage.

187
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:50,996
Good thing, no vital organs were hit.

188
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,211
Let’s pray there are no complications.

189
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:00,548
Can we see him?

190
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:02,758
He’ll be transferred to the ICU shortly.

191
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:06,428
So you may not be able to talk to him yet.

192
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:08,681
- Okay.
- Thank you very much.

193
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:17,940
What if I blow your head off?

194
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:18,899
Do it!

195
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,695
I’m your last chance to survive this.

196
00:14:22,778 --> 00:14:25,197
Because if anything bad happens to me,

197
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:27,408
good luck.

198
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,286
To your friends,

199
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,121
your bar,

200
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,832
and your entire family.

201
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:40,838
You think I’m afraid of Viktor?

202
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:49,388
He’s not who you should fear.

203
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:06,238
What happened at the event?

204
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:08,115
They took Donabel Valtrovi.

205
00:15:15,205 --> 00:15:16,582
Rody Salazar.

206
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:27,384
What did he do?

207
00:15:28,302 --> 00:15:30,387
He tried to assassinate Chiara,

208
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:32,306
but he hit our asset.

209
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,646
Fortunately, sir, no.

210
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:43,859
Why would Attorney
attempt an assassination?

211
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:52,201
Maybe force them to negotiate with them

212
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:54,161
to divide territories

213
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:56,956
or forge a truce between
the local syndicate

214
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:58,916
and the new foreign syndicate.

215
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:05,005
<i>Why did you operate out in the open?</i>

216
00:16:05,089 --> 00:16:07,216
<i>What got into your heads</i>

217
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:09,551
<i>to publicly challenge the Moravianos?</i>

218
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:13,222
It's better that the Moravianos
are openly challenged,

219
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:16,266
so the public learns about them.

220
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:19,603
So whatever they're hiding comes out.

221
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:21,271
After the events tonight,

222
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:24,024
they won't be able
to hide anything anymore.

223
00:16:24,108 --> 00:16:26,485
The public will smell their stench.

224
00:16:26,568 --> 00:16:29,446
<i>Do you think they won’t smell</i>
<i>our group as well?</i>

225
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,909
<i>So we don’t get implicated.</i>

226
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:38,122
<i>I have already manipulated</i>
<i>the entire agency to bring them down.</i>

227
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:46,380
<i>But you ruined all of that!</i>

228
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:49,883
You are a fool if you believe
that the Moravianos can be taken down

229
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:52,553
by your lousy government agency!

230
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:56,098
If the government
were the answer to the problem,

231
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:58,225
then the Philippines
would be developed by now!

232
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:03,939
Because the government
is the real syndicate!

233
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,527
What was meant to happen
has already happened.

234
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:13,657
And I will find Viktor,
wherever his hideout is!

235
00:17:14,616 --> 00:17:17,870
I will expose whatever dirt
they’re hiding.

236
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:19,663
Even if it means gunfire at Luneta.

237
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:21,123
I will challenge him!

238
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:23,000
Just to bring their dirt out!

239
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:24,668
The most complicated part here,

240
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:26,754
is this guy went rogue already.

241
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:27,713
So I think

242
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:29,631
this was not really planned
by the Sinigang cartel

243
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,759
to assassinate Chiara.

244
00:17:31,842 --> 00:17:35,471
It’s probably just
Attorney’s personal vendetta,

245
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:37,931
and they just want revenge on Viktor.

246
00:17:41,643 --> 00:17:44,396
Seems like you don’t have
approval from your bosses.

247
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,440
That’s not good.

248
00:17:47,983 --> 00:17:49,359
Of course,

249
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:52,112
if your bosses don’t like you,

250
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:54,990
your performance review goes down.

251
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:57,284
And if your performance review is low,

252
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:59,411
you won’t get a bonus. What a waste.

253
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:12,424
I’m sure

254
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:17,054
your conversations are always fun.

255
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:19,973
Of course!

256
00:18:26,313 --> 00:18:28,899
Where you can be killed
by your enemies anytime.

257
00:18:30,734 --> 00:18:36,323
You’ll realize you should
just enjoy the moment, every day.

258
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:38,951
I guess that’s our coping mechanism.
Right?

259
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:41,620
In another life,

260
00:18:42,996 --> 00:18:44,456
perhaps we would get along.

261
00:18:45,499 --> 00:18:47,668
<i>When we dug up Attorney’s body,</i>

262
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:51,463
it turns out he was the brother
of Congressman Celestino Salazar.

263
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:55,259
And it looks like he wants Viktor
to feel the same pain he went through.

264
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:57,928
Where is Attorney now?

265
00:18:58,011 --> 00:19:00,514
He is now in police custody,

266
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:04,017
but he had to be taken to the hospital
because he sustained minor injuries.

267
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:06,562
What do the police know now?

268
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:08,063
<i>I don’t know anything!</i>

269
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:11,358
If only I could,
I would tell those criminals

270
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:14,736
to not commit crimes
while I’m on vacation leave.

271
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,572
That’s not allowed!

272
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:19,741
I’ll just call you again, buddy.

273
00:19:23,453 --> 00:19:24,496
Can I ask a question, friend?

274
00:19:25,497 --> 00:19:27,875
Are you looking for a restroom?
There might be one at the end.

275
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:30,169
No, I peed already.

276
00:19:30,252 --> 00:19:31,837
I’m Mario Pinagpala.

277
00:19:36,466 --> 00:19:39,219
What is your relation
to the gunshot victim?

278
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:40,762
I’m his father.

279
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:46,602
Sir, I know you just need information,

280
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:50,564
but to be honest,
it’s still under investigation.

281
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:53,275
I understand that.

282
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:56,862
I just want to know if you have…

283
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:58,155
a theory.

284
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,574
Who would dare do something like this?

285
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:03,243
If you think about it, it’s very brazen.

286
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:04,953
The attack.

287
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,455
I mean, if it’s kidnapping

288
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:07,915
what they wanted to happen,

289
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:10,417
who would have the courage to kidnap

290
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:15,464
someone from a very prominent family
in a very public place?

291
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:19,968
Sir, do you have a background
in criminal investigation?

292
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,221
None.

293
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:24,640
Just curious.

294
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:27,643
Because no matter how you look at it,
from any angle,

295
00:20:29,311 --> 00:20:30,520
this is not normal.

296
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:41,281
But you’re right.

297
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:42,950
Even us,

298
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:46,745
we are surprised

299
00:20:46,828 --> 00:20:50,958
by how brazen this operation is.

300
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,834
Something like this

301
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:56,338
can only be done
by a very desperate group.

302
00:21:21,738 --> 00:21:24,032
Why aren’t we doing anything?

303
00:21:28,412 --> 00:21:31,039
We already know the cartel’s location.

304
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:37,462
Hey… Kian.

305
00:21:41,049 --> 00:21:43,677
- I know.
- And now you still want to save them.

306
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,012
- Who's also a Valtrovi.
- I know.

307
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:47,764
But a crime still took place.

308
00:21:47,848 --> 00:21:50,517
What are we going to do
with this information?

309
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,519
Just sit on it?

310
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:56,356
And there’s nothing we can do.

311
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:02,029
And we cannot interfere.

312
00:22:04,197 --> 00:22:05,073
Hey!

313
00:22:14,041 --> 00:22:16,001
In case you’ve forgotten.

314
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:25,343
But our agency doesn’t need
this kind of exposure.

315
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:32,309
And by launching a rescue operation
for Mrs. Valtrovi,

316
00:22:32,392 --> 00:22:34,644
it will just make it look like
we’re siding with a syndicate.

317
00:22:35,228 --> 00:22:37,689
Plus, if we rescue Donabel,

318
00:22:37,773 --> 00:22:40,484
they’ll find out we’ve been
monitoring the Moravianos.

319
00:22:43,403 --> 00:22:44,321
Wow.

320
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:50,035
Maybe there’s still something we can do.

321
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:52,996
What do you mean?

322
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:55,582
If we can’t act on this information,

323
00:22:56,374 --> 00:22:59,628
maybe we can pass it on to someone
who can actually use it.

324
00:23:25,487 --> 00:23:27,823
I have activated everyone

325
00:23:28,406 --> 00:23:30,408
to find your mother.

326
00:23:41,753 --> 00:23:45,006
Even if his punchlines are super corny.

327
00:23:54,349 --> 00:23:57,269
But he threw himself
in front of me to save me.

328
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:01,982
Child,

329
00:24:02,816 --> 00:24:04,818
I don’t think this is stupid.

330
00:24:21,835 --> 00:24:25,297
And I will make whoever
did this to Mikoy pay.

331
00:25:04,878 --> 00:25:06,421
- What’s happening?
- There’s a fire.

332
00:25:06,504 --> 00:25:08,423
- Where?
- In the security room.

333
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:09,966
<i>Fire in the security room?</i>

334
00:25:11,426 --> 00:25:13,470
<i>All CCTV controls are inside</i>
<i>the security room.</i>

335
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:15,597
<i>Security cameras are being sabotaged.</i>

336
00:25:18,975 --> 00:25:20,185
There’s someone who wants to talk to you.

337
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:34,616
<i>What will be left of you</i>
<i>is just peace of mind.</i>

